<HEADLINE> Items Sold at O.J. Simpson Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some of the items sold at an auction of O.J. Simpson belongings:  
</P>
<P>
	-- Heisman Trophy, $230,000  
</P>
<P>
	-- Football Hall of Fame award, $10,000  
</P>
<P>
	-- Life-size metal statue of Simpson, $3,250  
</P>
<P>
	-- University of Southern California Hall of Fame trophy, $1,800  
</P>
<P>
	-- Player of the year trophy from ABC Wide World of Sports in  
1973, $1,700 
</P>
<P>
	-- Associated Press certificates from 1967 and 1968 for being the  
best Southern California halfback and first team offense, $1,400 
</P>
<P>
	-- Two Tiffany-style lamps, $7,000 each  
</P>
<P>
	-- Painting of a girl given to Simpson by singer Donna Summer,  
$5,500 
</P>
<P>
	-- No. 32 football jersey, $4,500  
</P>
<P>
	-- Commemorative football, $2,250  
</P>
<P>
	-- Life-size tennis player figure $1,200  
</P>
<P>
	-- Commemorative NFL alumni umbrella, $400  
</P>
<P>
	-- Fox fur coat, $550  
</P>
